<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF206-962-016  </DOCNO><DOCID>06 962 016.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  Jan 16 1989 v6 n2 p26(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>C-based expert system tool ported to VMS. (Inference Corp.'sAutomated Reasoning Tool-Information Management-VMS) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Inference Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Automated Reasoning Tool (computer program).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesC Programming LanguageExpert SystemsProgram Development Tools.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>C-Based Expert System Tool Ported to VMSandM;LOS ANGELES -- Inference has announced the availability of AutomatedReasoning Tool-Information Management/VMS (ART-IM/VMS)--its C-based expertsystem tool--on VAX/VMS systems.andM;ART-IM/VMS will complement ART/VMS, Inference's development tool for expertsystems that runs on Lisp machines and is available for VAXes and SunMicrosystems workstations.andM;&quot;Inference has two product lines, one [ART/VMS] with powerful functionality,for scientists and engineers who need complicated expert systems, and ART-IM,for those who need speed,&quot; said Ted Marr, Inference's president and chiefoperating officer.andP;  &quot;ART-IM is for PCs, terminals and mainframes, and ART isaimed at workstations.andP;  They [users] can run applications from ART-IM on thePC, on the mainframe or in mixed mode,&quot; he said.andM;Since ART-IM already runs on PCs and IBM mainframes, this product will letprogrammers simultaneously develop applications that can easily be ported toand embedded into all of those environments.andP;  Users can also portapplications from ART-IM to ART, Marr said.andP;  He added that the DECworkstations announced last week will provide another opportunity for ART-IM.andM;&quot;It'll be perfect for us, and the users will love it because you've got evenmore compatibility,&quot; he said.andM;ART-IM/VMS is available now.andP;  Prices start at $10,000 for a developmentversion for the MicroVAX 2000 and runs to $60,000 for the 8800 series.andO;Run-time versions start at $2,000 and range to $30,000.andP;  Volume discounts areavailable.andM;Inference Corp. is located at 5300 W. Century Blvd., Los Angeles, CA 90045,(213) 417-7997.andO;</TEXT></DOC>